<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="384" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.117/31.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>453. Department’s 452, January 5. Representations made as directed. In
                            reply, French Minister for Foreign Affairs declines to intervene in
                            behalf of Chandeysson, using same arguments as in case Peralme, reported
                            in my 452.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
